title: CATER 155064, YCEM4B, Building 911, Rack 035, Level 06, Ch 14: MCOR does not trim.
text: YCEM4B (LTUS), Building 911, Rack 35, Level 06, Ch 014: measured MCOR output. -44 volts--basically railed. Does not respond to trim requests. Replaced module with spare from spares shelf in 911 (swapped daughter board over). At first, new module trims, but later lost trim and the output is once again railed with -44 volts out. Repeated trims don't work. Checked output cable jacks on the back of crate: NTF. ACR knobbed the output to zero. Will wait for software troubleshooting to see if this is a controls issue. The MCOR seems to work, just no control. Informed ACR if software fix doesn't work, replace the crate controller. If that doesn't work, may have to swap crate. MCOR in = MCOR2346; out = MCOR2084. DEPOT updated. Spares crate in B911 has 14 modules left in it. Placed suspect module in room 127 for ops check. CATER to remain open to see if software fix works.
